the saturday men is a 1962 british sports documentary about association football that follows a week in the life of west bromwich albion football club .   the film , the third episode of the three-part television series look at britain , was narrated by barney bamford and don howe .   it shows team members training and being given a pre-match talk by the club 's manager , archie macaulay , as well as footage of boardroom meetings .   there is also an interview with a footballer who is about to begin a new career as a salesman , and an appearance by a young bobby robson .   the episode was directed by john fletcher and written by denis mitchell , and was part of a series that looked at working class british life .   the other two films in the series are every day except christmas and we are the lambeth boys .   in july 2015 , the film was included in the british film institute 's online project , britain on film , which aims to build a social history of everyday british life .